Katsina State governor, Aminu Bello Masari has again urged the leadership of Christians in Nigeria to make the best use of churches in preaching peace and unity of the nation. Speaking when he received the president of Evangelical Church Winning All (ECWA),Â  Reverend Stephen Baba Panya, in his office at Government House, Katsina, he said the only way to make people understand the good side of the leadership and the conscious messages is by promoting peace and harmony among the diverse people of the country Observing that bad eggs among followers are usually responsible for the division and disharmony in the two common religions in Nigeria, reiterates the need for the Christian leadership to shun anything that would bring misunderstanding with their Muslim neighbours. On his part, the president of ECWA Reverend Stephen Baba Panya enjoined the state governor for the formation of Inter and Intra Religious Committee which he said will go a long way in promoting religious harmony in the state, explaining that the major difficulties facing the Christian community is obtaining a certificate of occupancy in building places of worship in the state. 